Business Brief -- Loewen Group Inc.:
   Acquisition Offer Is Planned
   For Toronto's Arbor Capital
Raymond Loewen, president and chief executive officer of
Loewen Group, said the company would be content to hold a
significant minority stake in Arbor.
   Loewen Group, based in Vancouver, British Colombia, and
the second-biggest funeral company in North America, said it
has received a commitment to purchase the Arbor shares
currently held by Tuckahoe Financial Corp. and Connor, Clark
 Co. The two companies, which are affiliated investment
management concerns based in Toronto, hold a combined 29% of
Arbor's Class A voting stock and 48% of the Class B nonvoting
shares.